#Amazon CloudWatch is a service that monitors Amazon Web Services (AWS) resources and applications. It can help you monitor performance, troubleshoot issues, and optimize resource use.

{ What can CloudWatch do? } 

Monitor applications, infrastructure, networks, and services
Collect and track metrics
Monitor log files
Set alarms
Respond to performance changes
Optimize resource use
Gain insights into operational health
Troubleshoot AWS infrastructure
Resolve technical issues
Streamline operations
